## Errors & Mistakes
From the original build (the code here carries the fixes):
1. Column AFFINITY was the biggest semantic gotcha: started_at > <numeric
   literal> must convert the literal to TEXT (sqlite affinity rules), or a
   real test (test_calls_query_stats_started_at_window_excludes_deletes)
   returns 3 instead of 0. Storage-class ordering alone is WRONG for plain
   columns.
2. Filter length validation originally lived in the per-record matcher and
   never fired on empty stores; it is hoisted to _validate_calls_filter.
3. The first evaluator interpreted the AST per record — 2.5x SLOWER than
   sqlite. The compile-once closure design here is the fix (1.4x+ faster);
   do not regress to per-row interpretation.

